      • getName

        public Name getName(NameType nameType)
        Retrieves a Name that belongs to this AbstractNamed that is appropriate for the supplied NameType, or null if no such Name can be found.

        This method may return null.

        Specified by:
        getName in interface Named
        Parameters:
        nameType - the NameType for which a Name will be sought; may be null in which case null will be returned
        Returns:
        a Name indexed under the supplied NameType, or null
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if nameType is not accepted for any reason

      • putName

        public Name putName(NameType nameType,
                    Name name)
        Stores the supplied Name under the supplied NameType in such a way that it can be retrieved later by the #getName(NameType)} method when that method is supplied with a NameType equal to the supplied NameType.

        Implementation Notes

        To properly orphan Names that are no longer indexed under a given NameType in this AbstractNamed, all the Names affiliated with this AbstractNamed implementation must be scanned, so this operation has performance that decreases as the total number of Names stored by this AbstractNamed implementation increases.

        Parameters:
        nameType - a NameType under which a new Name will be stored; must not be null
        name - a Name to store; must not be null; its Name.setNamed(Named) method will be called with this as its argument.
        Returns:
        the prior Name stored under the supplied NameType, or null if there was no such Name. The returned Name, if non-null, will return null from its Name.getNamed() method only if it is now truly orphaned, that is only if it is not indexed in this AbstractNamed under any other NameType.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if nameType or name is null, or if nameType is unsuitable, or if name is unsuitable

      • createName

        protected Name createName(NameValue nameValue)
        Creates a new Name implementation given a non-null NameValue.

        This implementation simply calls the relevant Name constructor.

        Parameters:
        nameValue - the NameValue that will serve as the value for the new Name; must not be null
        Returns:
        a new, non-null Name
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if nameValue is null
        See Also:
        Name.Name(Named, NameValue)

      • removeName

        public Name removeName(NameType nameType)
        Removes the single Name stored under a NameType that is equal or identical to the supplied NameType and returns it.

        This method may return null if there is no Name indexed under a NameType equal or identical to the supplied NameType.

        Parameters:
        nameType - the NameType to use to find the Name in question; must not be null
        Returns:
        the Name that was removed, or null. The Name that is returned, if non-null, will return null from its Name.getNamed() method.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if nameType is null
